      <hedline>
        <hl1>PATERSON PLAN</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By KAREN DeMASTERS</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>District superintendent Edwin Duroy says Paterson will need 10 new elementary schools, new high school, at cost of $570 million, and extensive renovations to existing schools in order to meet New Jersey Supreme Court's mandate to upgrade educational system (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Paterson, the state's third largest school district with 25,000 students, will need 10 new elementary schools, a new high school and extensive renovations to many remaining schools in order to meet the state Supreme Court's mandate to upgrade the educational system, said Edwin Duroy, the state-appointed superintendent in the district. The cost of construction alone will be $570 million.</p>
        <p>KAREN DeMASTERS</p>
      </block>
